testCases.explanation: With one duplicate 2, we get subsets: [], [1], [2], [1,2], [2,2], [1,2,2]. No duplicate subsets.
Empty input has one subset: the empty set.
Three duplicate 1s yield only 4 unique subsets: [], [1], [1,1], [1,1,1].

description:
Given an integer array `nums` that may contain duplicates, return all possible subsets (the power set).

The solution set must not contain duplicate subsets. Return the solution in any order.

See the full problem on [LeetCode 90](https://leetcode.com/problems/subsets-ii/).
